title: For Sale/Trade:  ISSC MK-22 Rifle
postcontent:
If your a fan of the FN-SCAR battle rifle, the MK22 should look very familiar. Along with the FN-style stock and receiver outline, the MK22 has many of the same features as the rifle that inspired it. The receiver is an all-metal construction, with a Picatinny-style rail system on all receiver surfaces. This includes a barrel placement for attaching FN sights. The mussle of the precision match, 16-inch barrel is cut with a 1:28 thread to accept various muzzle breaks and flash hiders.
 The three-position shoulder stock is adjustable for length, features a sling buckle mount and it has a two-position cheek rest that adjusts for height. The stock is fitted with a metal hinge to fold to the side with a polymer frame hook to lock the stock in the folded position for tactical training exercises. 
Comes with 22-round magazine. The adjustable front and rear rifle sights can be folded down to make room for a scope. When in the down position, the sights become a three-dot pistol system. 
The charging handle is part of the patent-pending Universal Charging Adaption System (UCAS), which allows the handle to be moved to three locations on the right or left side of the gun. The hollow grip is fitted with a removable base plate so it can be used for storage. Tan finish.

Along with this bill is an attempt to do away with all personal sales between private parties. It is now certain to be passed with a Democrat-controlled state congress. These magazines will quadruple in value as they did during the Clinton-era assault weapons ban, and Coloradans will no longer be able to purchase them, much the same as in New York or California.

Saiga .308. Has the rarer and no longer-manufactured lightweight wood furniture. Barrel length is 16" which is stiffer and more accurate than the 21" version. Comes with the following:

3x 25 round hi-cap magazines.
4x 8 round hunting-legal magazines.

6x42 illuminated rangefinding rifle scope with rubber lense covers and rail mount.
http://www.outdoorbunker.com/6-X-42-COMPACT-RANGEFINDER-SCOPE-p/%28ncs-straq642g-%29.htm

KVAR quick detach side-rail optic mount with mil-std rail
http://www.k-var.com/shop/Scope-Mounts/

Tech-sights rear-aperture HK-style sight and receiver buffer. Faster target acquisition, and much more accurate than standard AK sights.
http://www.tech-sights.com/ak.htm

OD sling

Additional side-rail optics mount, with top and side rails.
http://www.cheaperthandirt.com/product/AKS-006

Original receiver cover.


This functions flawlessly. There is roughly 500 rounds through it, without a single FTF or FTE. With good ammo, using the scope, it is capable of 1.5 inch groups at 100 yards. The only issue is that the front hand guard is a little loose. These are no longer for sale at any retailer, and are going to be on the immediate list of banned guns if the AWB passes by spring. If this does not sell, I have no problem keeping it as an investment.

Am open to trades for modern handguns, rifles, and revolvers, but I do not want your old military surplus clunkers, your hi-points, your single-action revolvers, or your 9mm ammo that you think is worth 40 cents a round. I reload, so I still get my ammo for reasonable prices. I am however interested in 5.45 ammunition as a partial trade, or straight across if you have a MASSIVE quantity of it.
